      "p",
      {
        "class": "intro"
      },
      "To get started with Ionic Framework, the only requirement is a ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#node-npm"
        },
        "Node & npm"
      ],
      " environment."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      {
        "class": "intro"
      },
      "Of course, a code editor is also required. ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://code.visualstudio.com/"
        },
        "Visual Studio Code"
      ],
      " is recommended. Visual Studio Code is a free, batteries-included text editor made by Microsoft."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "terminal"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#terminal"
        },
        "Terminal"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "blockquote",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "p",
        null,
        "Much of Ionic development requires familiarity with the command line. If you're new to the command line, see ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://ionicframework.com/blog/new-to-the-command-line/"
          },
          "this Blog Post"
        ],
        " for a quick introduction."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "In general, we recommend using the built-in terminals. Many third-party terminals work well with Ionic, but may not be supported."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "For Windows, ",
        [
          "strong",
          null,
          "Command Prompt"
        ],
        " and ",
        [
          "strong",
          null,
          "PowerShell"
        ],
        " are supported. ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/faq",
            "target": "_blank"
          },
          "WSL"
        ],
        " is known to work with Ionic, but may not be supported."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "For macOS, the built-in ",
        [
          "strong",
          null,
          "Terminal"
        ],
        " app is supported."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Git Bash (from ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://git-scm.com",
          "target": "_blank"
        },
        "git-scm.com"
      ],
      ") does not support TTY interactivity and is ",
      [
        "strong",
        null,
        "not supported"
      ],
      " by Ionic."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "node-npm"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#node-npm"
        },
        "Node & npm"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Almost all tooling for modern JavaScript projects is based in ",
      [
        "stencil-route-link",
        {
          "url": "/docs/reference/glossary#node"
        },
        "Node.js"
      ],
      ". The ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://nodejs.org/en/download/"
        },
        "download page"
      ],
      " has prebuilt installation packages for all platforms. We recommend selecting the LTS version to ensure best compatibility."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Node is bundled with ",
      [
        "stencil-route-link",
        {
          "url": "/docs/reference/glossary#npm"
        },
        "npm"
      ],
      ", the package manager for JavaScript."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "To verify the installation, open a new terminal window and run:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "node --version\n",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token function"
            },
            "npm"
          ],
          " --version"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "blockquote",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "p",
        null,
        "Permission errors are common on macOS when installing global packages with ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "npm"
        ],
        ". If you get an ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "EACCES"
        ],
        " error, see ",
        [
          "stencil-route-link",
          {
            "url": "/docs/developing/tips#resolving-permission-errors"
          },
          "Resolving Permission Errors"
        ],
        "."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "git"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#git"
        },
        "Git"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Although not required, the version control system ",
      [
        "stencil-route-link",
        {
          "url": "/docs/reference/glossary#git"
        },
        "Git"
      ],
      " is highly recommended."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Git is often accompanied by a Git Host, such as ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://github.com/"
        },
        "GitHub"
      ],
      ", in which case additional setup is required. Follow the tutorial from the Git Host's documentation to set up Git:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "GitHub: ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://help.github.com/en/articles/set-up-git"
          },
          "Set up Git"
        ]
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "GitLab: ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/topics/git/how_to_install_git"
          },
          "Installing Git"
        ]
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Bitbucket: ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/install-git"
          },
          "Install Git"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Otherwise, follow the ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git"
        },
        "official installation instructions"
      ],
      ". The command-line utility can be downloaded from the ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://git-scm.com/downloads"
        },
        "download page"
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "To verify the installation, open a new terminal window and run:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
